---
icon: "money-bill-1-wave"
title: "Economy"
description: "Economy is a currency system that can increase server engagement, rewarding members through jobs, daily bonuses, and games."
---

### Simple Setup

`,economy settings enable` - Enables Economy Module

`,economy settings amount 500`  - Sets the starting amount to 500 (Adjustable)

### Managing Economy in your server

<AccordionGroup>
  <Accordion title="Enable Economy" defaultOpen={false}>
    You can easily enable the economy module in your server by using the `,economy settings enable` command.

    ```plaintext
    ,economy settings enable
    ```
  </Accordion>

  <Accordion title="Disable Economy" defaultOpen={false}>
    You can easily disable the economy module in your server by using the `,economy settings disable` command.

    ```plaintext
    ,economy settings disable
    ```
  </Accordion>

  <Accordion title="Edit the starting amount for users" defaultOpen={false}>
    You can edit the amount that users start with by using the command below.

    <CodeGroup>
      ```plaintext Syntax
      ,economy settings amount (amount)
      ```

      ```plaintext Example
      ,economy settings amount 1500
      ```
    </CodeGroup>
  </Accordion>

  <Accordion title="Setting the claim amount" defaultOpen={false}>
    Sets the amount earned from claiming daily, weekly, or monthly rewards.&#x20;

    <CodeGroup>
      ```plaintext Syntax
      ,economy settings claimamount ('daily', 'weekly' or 'monthly') (amount)
      ```

      ```plaintext Example
      ,economy settings claimamount daily 100
      ,economy settings claimamount weekly 500
      ,economy settings claimamount monthly 2000
      ```
    </CodeGroup>
  </Accordion>

  <Accordion title="Setting the currency name and symbol" defaultOpen={false}>
    Set the currency name and symbol for your server.&#x20;

    <Warning>
      If you are using a custom emoji, make sure that it is accessible to Loti, or else commands may not function properly.
    </Warning>

    <CodeGroup>
      ```plaintext Syntax
      ,economy settings currency (currency name) (currency symbol)
      ```

      ```plaintext Example
      ,economy settings currency coins 💰
      ```
    </CodeGroup>
  </Accordion>

  <Accordion title="Reset Economy Settings" defaultOpen={false}>
    <Warning>
      This will reset the economy settings for the server to default values.

      ```plaintext
      ,economy settings reset
      ```
    </Warning>
  </Accordion>

  <Accordion title="Add Jobs" defaultOpen={false}>
    Adds a new job to the server.&#x20;

    <CodeGroup>
      ```plaintext Syntax
      /job add (job_name) (job_description) (pay_amount) (exp needed)
      ```

      ```plaintext Example
      /job add photographer take photos! 3800 130
      ```
    </CodeGroup>
  </Accordion>

  <Accordion title="Edit Jobs" defaultOpen={false}>
    Edits existing jobs in the server.

    <CodeGroup>
      ```plaintext Syntax
      /job edit (job name) (new description) (new pay amount) (exp needed)
      ```

      ```plaintext Example
      /job edit photographer take photos! 3500 120
      ```
    </CodeGroup>
  </Accordion>
</AccordionGroup>

### Using the Economy Commands

<AccordionGroup>
  <Accordion title="Open an Account" defaultOpen={false}>
    Open an economy account in the server.

    ```plaintext
    ,open
    ```
  </Accordion>

  <Accordion title="Viewing Balance" defaultOpen={false}>
    You can view your balance, or someone else's balance by using the command below.

    <CodeGroup>
      ```plaintext Syntax
      ,balance {optional: user}
      ```

      ```plaintext View your own balance
      ,balance
      ```

      ```plaintext View someone else's balance
      ,balance @blahja
      ```
    </CodeGroup>
  </Accordion>

  <Accordion title="Claiming your Reward" defaultOpen={false}>
    Claim your daily, weekly, or monthly reward.

    <Tip>
      These amounts can be edited through the economy settings.
    </Tip>

    <CodeGroup>
      ```plaintext Syntax
      ,claim ('daily', 'weekly' or 'monthly')
      ```

      ```plaintext Examples
      ,claim daily
      ,claim weekly
      ,claim monthly
      ```
    </CodeGroup>
  </Accordion>

  <Accordion title="Select a Job" defaultOpen={false}>
    Select a job to earn coins.

    <CodeGroup>
      ```plaintext Syntax
      ,job select (job)
      ```

      ```plaintext Example
      ,job select fisher
      ```
    </CodeGroup>
  </Accordion>

  <Accordion title="Work at your Job" defaultOpen={false}>
    Work to earn coins.

    ```plaintext
    ,job work
    ```
  </Accordion>

  <Accordion title="Quit your Job" defaultOpen={false}>
    Quit your current job.

    ```
    ,job quit
    ```
  </Accordion>

  <Accordion title="View the Avaliable Jobs" defaultOpen={false}>
    List the available jobs.

    <Tip>
      Jobs can be added or changed, reference above to see how!
    </Tip>

    ```plaintext
    ,job list
    ```
  </Accordion>

  <Accordion title="Play the Slot Machine" defaultOpen={false}>
    Play slots to win coins.

    <CodeGroup>
      ```plaintext Syntax
      ,slots (amount)
      ```

      ```plaintext Example
      ,slots 100
      ```
    </CodeGroup>
  </Accordion>

  <Accordion title="Play Blackjack" defaultOpen={false}>
    Play blackjack to win coins.

    <CodeGroup>
      ```plaintext Syntax
      ,blackjack (amount)
      ```

      ```plaintext Example
      ,blackjack 100
      ```
    </CodeGroup>
  </Accordion>

  <Accordion title="Flip a Coin" defaultOpen={false}>
    Flip a coin to win coins.

    <CodeGroup>
      ```plaintext Syntax
      ,coinflip (amount) ('heads' or 'tails')
      ```

      ```plaintext Example
      ,coinflip 100 tails
      ```
    </CodeGroup>
  </Accordion>

  <Accordion title="Send coins to another user" defaultOpen={false}>
    Send coins to another user.

    <CodeGroup>
      ```plaintext Syntax
      ,transfer (user) (amount)
      ```

      ```plaintext Example
      ,transfer @blahja 1000
      ```
    </CodeGroup>
  </Accordion>
</AccordionGroup>